{"page_id": "https://www.nytimes.com/1984/09/06/opinion/nominations-for-civil-court-tuesday-s-primary-voters-will-pick-their-party-s.html", "source": "nyt", "arm": "elections", "window": "1984", "newspaper_title": "The New York Times", "lccn": null, "date": "1984-09-06", "state": null, "city": null, "type_of_material": "Editorial", "section": "Opinion", "ocr_text": "Nominations for the Civil Court In Tuesday's primary, voters will pick their party's nominees for Civil Court judgeship races in the November election. Civil Court judges are elected to 10-year terms by countywide vote or by district. They handle matters involving less than $25,000 but may serve as acting Supreme Court justices and sit anywhere in the city. Here are our choices in contested Democratic races; there are no contests among Republican candidates.", "matched_phrase": "will be elected", "cycle": 1984}
